Linux stores logs inside the systemd journal.

Useful commands:

```bash
journalctl
journalctl -n 20
journalctl -b
journalctl -f
```

---

## Key Takeaways

- Services provide background functionality.
- systemctl manages services.
- journalctl displays system logs.
