# File Compression & Archiving

## tar

Creates archives containing multiple files.

Common commands

```bash
tar -cvf archive.tar folder/
tar -tvf archive.tar
tar -xvf archive.tar
```

---

## gzip

Compresses files.

Commands

```bash
gzip file
gunzip file.gz
```

---

## zip

Archives and compresses simultaneously.

Commands

```bash
zip backup.zip *.txt
unzip backup.zip
```

---

## Why Compression is Used

- Saves storage
- Faster transfers
- Easier backups
- Maintains directory structure
# Linux Special Permissions

## SUID

Runs a program with the file owner's permissions.

Example:

```bash
ls -l /usr/bin/passwd
```

---

## SGID

Files inherit group ownership.

Useful for collaborative directories.

---

## Sticky Bit

Users can delete only their own files inside shared directories.

Example:

```bash
ls -ld /tmp
```

---

